Police top brass say the community must step up to report criminals. But crime volunteers say they need more support to help keep their communities safe. Lindsay Dentlinger reports. Courtesy #dstv403 CAPE TOWN - The proliferation of weapons, extortion rackets, and gangsterism are among the crimes of concern raised at a summit in Khayelitsha. Police top brass say the community must step up to report criminals. WATCH: Crime Summit | Khayelitsha youth sad and scared But crime volunteers say they need more support to help keep their communities safe. South Africa’s new police commissioner says the community plays a vital role in getting a grip on crime in Khayelitsha. * eNCA's Lindsay Dentlinger reports.